<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,628,943]" pageId="11" pageNumber="194">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,736,762]" pageId="11" pageNumber="194">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng" authorityYear="1998" box="[280,537,736,762]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Systolederus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emeiensis">
<emphasis box="[280,537,736,762]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="194">Systolederus emeiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not a 
<taxonomicName box="[631,860,736,762]" pageId="11" pageNumber="194">
<emphasis box="[631,773,736,762]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="194">Systolederus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
because eyes not draw to each other in front giving the triangular shape to vertex; vertex well depressed, lateral margins of vertex turned backward and elevated up to upper margin of eyes. It belongs to 
<taxonomicName authority="Bolivar, 1817" authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1817" box="[563,798,808,834]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[563,631,809,834]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="194">Xistra</emphasis>
Bolívar, 1817
</taxonomicName>
. We have examined the 
<typeStatus box="[1079,1127,809,835]" pageId="11" pageNumber="194">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng" authorityYear="1998" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Systolederus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emeiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="194">Systolederus emeiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng" authorityYear="2009" box="[320,508,845,870]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yaanensis">
<emphasis box="[320,508,845,870]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="194">Xistra yaanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and found that structures and coloration of the body are the same in both taxa. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng" authorityYear="2009" box="[275,460,881,906]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yaanensis">
<emphasis box="[275,460,881,906]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="194">Xistra yaanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here considered a synonym of of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng" authorityYear="1998" box="[863,1120,880,906]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Systolederus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emeiensis">
<emphasis box="[863,1120,880,906]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="194">Systolederus emeiensis</emphasis>
